parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates without warning
often when braking or shifting gears
and may continue to accelerate even when the brake pedal is pressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Throttle Body or Accelerator Pedal Assembly
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty throttle body or accelerator pedal assembly can cause unintended acceleration, leading to accidents and injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience sudden acceleration
and the accelerator pedal may stick or fail to return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electronic system failures can cause unintended acceleration, stalling, or other safety issues, leading to accidents and injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle's electronic systems may malfunction
causing the vehicle to accelerate or decelerate unexpectedly
or fail to respond to driver input.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Head Bolt Stripping and Head Gasket Failure

The failure of the intake manifold can cause the engine to stall, leading to loss of power and potentially causing accidents.
The failure of the throttle body can cause the engine to stall or hesitate, leading to loss of power and potentially causing accidents.
The failure of the engine cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to catastrophic engine failure and potentially causing accidents.
The failure of the timing chain can cause the engine to stall or hesitate, leading to loss of power and potentially causing accidents.
